		<Placemark id="05DDD6E2AF3EAF18E0EF">
		<name>Jurong Island SUPER refinery </name>
		<description><![CDATA[<div>It’s a <b>refinery and terminal complex</b> located on <b><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Jurong Island. SRC is jointly owned by: Chevron &amp; PetroChina&nbsp;</span></span></b><br></div><div><b><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal"></span></span></b><br></div><div>Refines crude oil into:<br></div><li><ul><li>Jet fuel<br></li><li>Diesel<br></li><li>Gasoline<br></li></ul></li><li><div>Has:<br></div><ul><li>Storage tanks<br></li><li>Marine jetties (for ship loading)<br></li></ul></li><div><br></div>]]></description>
		<LookAt>
			<longitude>103.7097871214256</longitude>
			<latitude>1.284803277403461</latitude>
			<altitude>6.188865349213478</altitude>
			<heading>0</heading>
			<tilt>0</tilt>
			<gx:fovy>35</gx:fovy>
			<range>7031.367921485798</range>
			<altitudeMode>absolute</altitudeMode>
		</LookAt>
		<styleUrl>#__managed_style_0DF9DA3C994081E8903F</styleUrl>
		<Point>
			<coordinates>103.7066291049394,1.28024302186643,6.231730153402673</coordinates>
		</Point>
	</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="0EBC51FC5A3EB1471A50">
		<name>Jamnagar SUPER Refinery </name>
		<description><![CDATA[<li><b>Owned by </b><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal"><b>Reliance Industries.&nbsp;</b></span></span><b></b><br></li><ul><li><b>Total capacity: </b><b>~1.2 million barrels per day</b><b></b><br></li><li><b>Actually </b><b>two refineries combined</b><b> in one complex</b><b></b><br></li><li><b>One of the most complex and advanced refining setups globally</b><br></li></ul><h2>1. DTA Refinery (older one)<br></h2><ul><li>Built first (late 1990s)<br></li><li>Called <b>Domestic Tariff Area (DTA)</b> refinery<br></li></ul><p><br></p><div>📍 On your image:<br></div><div>👉 <b>Left side (more compact layout)</b><br></div><p><br></p><div><hr><br></div><h2>🟦 2. SEZ Refinery (newer one)<br></h2><ul><li>Built later (~2008)<br></li><li>Located in a <b>Special Economic Zone (SEZ)</b><br></li></ul><p><br></p><div>📍 On your image:<br></div><div>👉 <b>Right side (bigger, more modern, more grid-like)</b><br></div><p><br></p><div><hr><br></div><h1>⚙️ 2) Why build two separate refineries?<br></h1><p>This is key to understanding “super refineries” 👇<br></p><h3>🟨 Different business models<br></h3><ul><li><div><b>DTA refinery</b><br></div><ul><li>Supplies India’s domestic market<br></li></ul></li><li><div><b>SEZ refinery</b><br></div><ul><li>Focuses on <b>exports</b><br></li><li>Tax advantages (SEZ rules)<br></li></ul></li></ul><div><hr><br></div><h3>🟩 Extreme flexibility<br></h3><p>Together they can:<br></p><ul><li><div>Process many types of crude:<br></div><ul><li>Heavy<br></li><li>Sour<br></li><li>Cheap discounted oil<br></li></ul></li></ul><p>👉 This is why traders love Jamnagar:<br></p><blockquote><p>It can optimize margins better than most refineries<br></p></blockquote><div><hr><br></div><h1>🔗 3) But they operate like ONE system<br></h1><p>Even though they are separate:<br></p><pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><br></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼk ͼy"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><div><span>Refinery 1  →\</span><br></div><div><span>              → shared infrastructure → export terminals</span><br></div><div><span>Refinery 2  →/</span><br></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div><br></div></div></div></div></div></pre><p>They share:<br></p><ul><li>Pipelines<br></li><li>Storage tanks<br></li><li>Port facilities<br></li><li>Utilities<br></li></ul><p>👉 So:<br></p><blockquote><p>Physically two refineries, functionally one mega-hub<br></p></blockquote><div><hr><br></div><h1>🧠 4) What you’re seeing in your image<br></h1><p>Let’s decode your screenshot:<br></p><h3>🟥 Left block<br></h3><ul><li>Older refinery (DTA)<br></li><li>Slightly less dense<br></li></ul><div><hr><br></div><h3>🟦 Right block<br></h3><ul><li>Newer SEZ refinery<br></li><li>Much larger + more structured<br></li></ul><div><hr><br></div><h3>🟪 Middle / surrounding<br></h3><ul><li>Petrochemicals (like the rubber plant you saw)<br></li><li>Utilities, storage, logistics<br></li></ul><div><br></div>]]></description>
