		<Placemark id="0374211D203F382D045A">
		<name>plant at Kandla, Gujarat</name>
		<description><![CDATA[<div>Owned by&nbsp;<span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; text-decoration: none; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: 300; letter-spacing: -0.36px; float: none; display: inline;"><span class="font" style="font-family: AkkuratPro-regular;"><span class="size" style="font-size: 18px;">L&amp;T Energy GreenTech, a subsidiary of Larsen &amp; Toubro</span></span></span><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>Industrial energy and logistics complex located within the Kandla (Deendayal) Port area in Gujarat, India. The facilities include liquid bulk storage tanks, petroleum and chemical handling infrastructure, marine loading jetties, rail-linked logistics yards, and cargo transfer systems supporting regional and international trade. The site serves as a strategic hub for fuel storage, bulk liquid imports/exports, shipping operations, and industrial supply chains along India’s western coast. The port-industrial zone is also expected to play a future role in India’s green energy transition, including potential green hydrogen and renewable ammonia export infrastructure.<br></div><div><br></div><div>From S&amp;P Global Energy News :&nbsp;<br></div><div>L&amp;T Energy GreenTech, a subsidiary of Larsen &amp; Toubro, has signed a long-term agreement with Japan's Itochu Corp to supply 300,000 metric tons/year of renewable ammonia from its proposed plant at Kandla, Gujarat, L&amp;T said. L&amp;T Energy GreenTech will supply renewable ammonia to Itochu on a captive, take-or-pay basis, building on the Joint Development Agreement between the companies signed in July 2025. The agreement with Itochu is a significant step in translating L&amp;T's clean energy ambitions into large-scale, bankable projects, according to Subramanian Sarma, deputy managing director and president at L&amp;T.<br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
