	</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="08E95E6E1D3EB7332679">
		<name>Parks I &amp; Parks II Nuclear Power Plant (being built)</name>
		<description><![CDATA[<h1>1) What exactly is being built?<br></h1><ul><li><b>2 new nuclear reactors</b> (Russian design: VVER-1200)<br></li><li>Total capacity: <b>~2,400 MW</b><br></li><li>Built by Russia’s state nuclear company: <b><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Rosatom</span></span></b><br></li><li>Financed largely by a <b>Russian state loan (~€10 billion)</b><br></li></ul><p>👉 Once completed, it will <b>double Hungary’s nuclear generation capacity</b>.<br></p><h1>2) Why it matters for Hungary<br></h1><p>Hungary already relies heavily on nuclear power:<br></p><ul><li>The existing Paks plant supplies <b>~50% of Hungary’s electricity</b><br></li><li><div>Paks II will:<br></div><ul><li>Replace aging reactors<br></li><li>Keep electricity <b>low-cost and stable</b><br></li><li>Reduce reliance on imported fossil fuels<br></li></ul></li></ul><p>👉 So in simple terms:<br></p><blockquote><p>Paks II = Hungary’s long-term energy security strategy<br></p></blockquote><h1>3) Why it’s politically controversial<br></h1><p>This is where your quote comes in.<br></p><h3>🇷🇺 Strong Russia link<br></h3><ul><li>Built by <b>Rosatom</b><br></li><li>Uses <b>Russian technology + buyes oil from Lukoil &amp; Rosneft (100k b/d 2025) ~ 90% of its supply</b><br></li><li>Funded by <b>Russian financing</b><br></li></ul><p>👉 Critics say this:<br></p><ul><li>Deepens Hungary’s dependence on Russia<br></li><li>Conflicts with EU efforts to reduce Russian influence<br></li></ul><div><br></div><h3>🇺🇸 Sanctions angle (your quote)<br></h3><p>After Russia’s invasion of Ukraine:<br></p><ul><li>Many Russian energy projects were sanctioned<br></li><li><b>Paks II got caught in that pressure</b><br></li></ul><p>But:<br></p><ul><li>Hungary argued it’s <b>civil nuclear energy (not gas/oil)</b><br></li><li>The US eventually <b>lifted sanctions affecting the project</b><br></li></ul><p>👉 That’s what your S&amp;P excerpt refers to:<br></p><blockquote><p>Hungary regained the ability to continue building Paks II<br></p></blockquote><div><br></div>]]></description>
		<LookAt>
			<longitude>18.85607054366088</longitude>
			<latitude>46.57626525673856</latitude>
			<altitude>97.61853345271325</altitude>
			<heading>0</heading>
			<tilt>0</tilt>
			<gx:fovy>35</gx:fovy>
			<range>2510.807458990021</range>
			<altitudeMode>absolute</altitudeMode>
		</LookAt>
		<styleUrl>#__managed_style_2EEEAD85BD4081E89038</styleUrl>
		<Point>
			<coordinates>18.85124342855411,46.57475419095047,100.7972703777043</coordinates>
		</Point>
	</Placemark>
