		<Placemark id="0DD0B927323F53B1392C">
		<name>Sakhalin - 2 route</name>
		<description><![CDATA[<h2>What is the Sakhalin-2 project?<br></h2><p><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Sakhalin Energy</span></span> operates the <span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Sakhalin-2 Project</span></span>.<br></p><p>It is one of Russia’s largest integrated:<br></p><ul><li>offshore oil,<br></li><li>offshore gas,<br></li><li>LNG export projects.<br></li></ul><p>The project includes:<br></p><h3>1. Offshore fields<br></h3><p>Main offshore fields:<br></p><ul><li>Piltun-Astokhskoye<br></li><li>Lunskoye<br></li></ul><p>These fields produce:<br></p><ul><li>crude oil,<br></li><li>natural gas.<br></li></ul><div><hr><br></div><h3>2. Pipelines across Sakhalin Island<br></h3><p>Hydrocarbons are transported southward across the island through pipelines.<br></p><div><hr><br></div><h3>3. Prigorodnoye LNG plant<br></h3><p>At the south of the island:<br></p><ul><li>gas is liquefied into LNG,<br></li><li>oil is exported by tanker.<br></li></ul><p>This is where the cargo in your article was loaded.<br></p><div><hr><br></div><h2>What is Sakhalin Blend crude?<br></h2><p>“Sakhalin Blend” is the crude oil exported from the Sakhalin-2 project.<br></p><p>It is:<br></p><ul><li>light crude,<br></li><li>sweet crude (low sulfur),<br></li><li>attractive for Asian refiners.<br></li></ul><p>The interesting point is that this oil is partly produced alongside LNG operations.<br></p><p>That is why sanctions exemptions exist:<br></p><blockquote><p>if Japan stopped taking Sakhalin crude, it could disrupt the entire LNG chain feeding Japan.<br></p></blockquote><div><hr><br></div><h2>Why is Japan still importing it?<br></h2><p>Japan depends heavily on LNG imports for power generation.<br></p><p>The <span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Sakhalin-2 Project</span></span> supplies LNG directly to Japanese utilities because:<br></p><ul><li>shipping distance is short,<br></li><li>supply is stable,<br></li><li><div>Japan already owns minority stakes through:<br></div><ul><li><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Mitsui &amp; Co.</span></span><br></li><li><span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Mitsubishi Corporation</span></span><br></li></ul></li></ul><p>So the US and G7 created a specific exemption allowing Japan to continue importing Sakhalin-related crude and LNG.<br></p><div><br></div>]]></description>
